---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Website Terms" description="Terms for using the Spires Digital website, articles and free ecommerce planning tools.">
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Website terms' }]} />
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="container page-hero-content"><span class="badge">Legal</span><h1>Website terms</h1><p>Last updated: 18 July 2026</p></div></section>
  <section class="section surface"><div class="container legal-content">
    <p class="lead">These terms apply to spiresdigital.com. A signed proposal or client agreement will contain the terms for any paid work and will take precedence for that engagement.</p>
    <h2>1. Information, not a guarantee</h2><p>The website provides general marketing information and planning aids. It is not financial, legal or tax advice. Examples, estimates and calculator outputs depend on the assumptions supplied and do not guarantee future performance.</p>
    <h2>2. Free tools</h2><p>Calculator and assessment results are indicative. You are responsible for checking inputs, formulas and commercial decisions against your own records. Tool inputs are processed in your browser unless a page clearly states otherwise.</p>
    <h2>3. Platform and third-party information</h2><p>Advertising platforms, ecommerce software, tax rules and third-party services can change after publication. Check current primary sources and obtain qualified advice where the decision requires it.</p>
    <h2>4. Intellectual property</h2><p>Unless otherwise stated, the original text, design and software on this website belong to Spires Digital. You may link to and quote short extracts with attribution. You may not republish substantial parts or present the tools as your own without written permission.</p>
    <h2>5. Acceptable use</h2><p>Do not attempt to disrupt the website, bypass security, introduce malicious code, scrape it in a way that impairs service, or use the contact forms for unlawful or abusive communications.</p>
    <h2>6. External links</h2><p>Links to other websites are provided for context. Spires Digital does not control their availability, security, content or privacy practices.</p>
    <h2>7. Availability and liability</h2><p>We aim to keep the website accurate and available but provide it without warranties to the extent permitted by law. Spires Digital is not responsible for losses arising solely from reliance on general website content or indicative tool outputs. Nothing in these terms limits liability where it cannot lawfully be limited.</p>
    <h2>8. Privacy</h2><p>Our <a href="/privacy">privacy notice</a> explains how contact, attribution and consent information is handled.</p>
    <h2>9. Changes</h2><p>We may update the website and these terms. The date above shows the latest published version.</p>
    <h2>10. Contact and governing law</h2><p>Spires Digital is run from Guernsey. These website terms are governed by the laws of the Bailiwick of Guernsey, and its courts have jurisdiction, subject to any mandatory consumer rights that apply. Questions can be sent to <a href="mailto:jack@spiresdigital.com">jack@spiresdigital.com</a>.</p>
  </div></section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-content { max-width: 790px; }
  .legal-content .lead { color: var(--ink); font-size: 1.15rem; }
  .legal-content h2 { margin: 2.4rem 0 .7rem; font-size: 1.45rem; }
  .legal-content p { margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--slate); line-height: 1.8; }
  .legal-content a { color: var(--violet-dark); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
</style>
